{
  "formatVersion": "1.0.0",
  "title": "Nuclei segmentation slides content",
  "rounds": [
    {
      "id": "r-1",
      "kind": "claude",
      "prompt": "Open @tests/examples/Osteosarcoma_01.tif with the Fiji-MCP.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "s-1",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "assistant",
            "html": "<p>Opening the image in Fiji via MCP — let me take a look.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-2",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "window",
            "windowTitle": "Osteosarcoma_01.tif",
            "content": {
              "kind": "fiji-image",
              "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_001.png",
              "statusBar": "1376×1104 pixels; RGB"
            },
            "subtitle": "1376×1104 · RGB · fluorescence"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-3",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "comment": "Claude identifies the fluorescence channels automatically — DAPI (blue) for nuclei, green for cytoskeleton.",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "assistant",
            "html": "<p>The image is open — a fluorescence micrograph of osteosarcoma cells. Blue (DAPI) marks nuclei, green marks cytoskeleton.</p>",
            "final": true,
            "slideDuration": 4000
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r-2",
      "kind": "claude",
      "prompt": "Segment the nuclei. Try 8 different approaches to tune parameters, compare them, and pick the best.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "s-4",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "assistant",
            "html": "<p>I'll extract the blue channel and try 8 thresholding strategies — from simple Otsu to morphological cleanup with Watershed.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-5",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "window",
            "windowTitle": "Approaches 1–4",
            "content": {
              "kind": "window-collection",
              "rows": 2,
              "cols": 2,
              "windows": [
                {
                  "title": "#1 Otsu (raw)",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_003.png"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "title": "#2 Triangle",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_004.png"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "title": "#3 Li",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_005.png"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "title": "#4 Gaussian + Otsu",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_006.png"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "subtitle": "Basic thresholding methods",
            "slideDuration": 2500
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-6",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "window",
            "windowTitle": "Approaches 5–8",
            "content": {
              "kind": "window-collection",
              "rows": 2,
              "cols": 2,
              "windows": [
                {
                  "title": "#5 Median + Otsu + WS",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_008.png"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "title": "#6 Phansalkar (local)",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_010.png"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "title": "#7 Gauss + Otsu + Open + WS ★",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_011.png"
                  }
                },
                {
                  "title": "#8 Huang + WS",
                  "content": {
                    "kind": "image",
                    "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_012.png"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "subtitle": "Advanced methods",
            "slideDuration": 2500
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-7",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "assistant",
            "html": "<p>Approach #7 looks cleanest — running Analyze Particles to count nuclei.</p>",
            "final": false
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-8",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "window",
            "windowTitle": "Nuclei Segmentation Result",
            "content": {
              "kind": "fiji-image",
              "src": "tutorials/nuclei-segmentation/assets/step_014.png",
              "statusBar": "103 nuclei detected · Approach #9"
            },
            "subtitle": "103 nuclei — Osteosarcoma_01.tif"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "s-9",
          "included": true,
          "displayMode": "full",
          "inserted": {
            "type": "assistant",
            "html": "<p><strong>103 nuclei</strong> segmented using <strong>Approach #7</strong> — Gaussian blur + Otsu threshold + Morphological Open + Watershed.</p><p>#7's morphological Open step removed debris and thin bridges before Watershed, producing the cleanest nucleus shapes out of all 10 approaches.</p>",
            "final": true,
            "slideDuration": 7000
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
